modules.description: Manages WebSocket-based subscription states with operations to add, remove, and notify subscribers. It works with subscription identifiers and callback functions to handle incoming events. Used to route real-time data updates to connected clients over WebSocket connections.

Manages WebSocket subscriptions with operations to register callbacks, handle incoming messages, and route real-time events to clients. It works with GraphQL variables, subscription IDs, and WebSocket descriptors to facilitate live data updates over persistent connections. Used to implement server-side subscription handling for GraphQL over WebSockets.
